ezium\u003C/strong\u003E is part of the distal row of carpal bones. The distal row consists of the trapezium, trapezoid, capitate, and hamate.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options are part of the proximal row:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EScaphoid\u003C/strong\u003E - This is part of the proximal row\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELunate\u003C/strong\u003E - This is part of the proximal row\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPisiform\u003C/strong\u003E - This is part of the proximal row\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETriquetrum\u003C/strong\u003E - This is part of the proximal row\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The carpal bones are divided into two rows: proximal and distal.","The distal row of carpal bones includes the trapezium, trapezoid, capitate, and hamate.","The proximal row of carpal bones includes the scaphoid, lunate, triquetrum, and pisiform."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30521257","Paulsen, F., \u0026 Waschke, J. (Eds.). (2023). Sobotta Atlas of Anatomy, Vol. 1, English/Latin: General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System (Vol. 1). Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63760"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18126"}},"